description: From Middle English ther-oute, þer-out, þar-out, þeroute, from Old English þǣrūt and þǣrūte, equivalent to there +‎ out. Compare Saterland Frisian deeruut, Dutch daaruit, German Low German daarut, German daraus.

entries.meaning: (archaic) Out of it, out from it.
examples: Thereout a strange beast with seven heads arose, / That townes and castles under her brest did coure.
